3.2 Cazymes

cazymes <- read.delim("~/Git/UPSCb/projects/aspen-cazymes/src/R/CAZYlist_Poplar_20180825.txt",as.is=TRUE)
cazymes <- cazymes[!duplicated(cazymes[,1]),]

Not all cazymes are in Aspwood

sprintf("%s cazymes out of %s are present in the aspwood dataset",sum(cazymes[,1] %in% row.names(vst)),nrow(cazymes))
## [1] "1188 cazymes out of 1916 are present in the aspwood dataset"

Fetching those that are

caz.dat <- na.omit(as.matrix(vst[cazymes[,1],grep("K1",colnames(vst))]))
stopifnot(all(rownames(caz.dat) %in% cazymes[,1]))

Writing them down

write.csv(caz.dat,file="Cazymes-GT106_aspwood-vst-expression-data_tree-K1.csv")

4 Expression specificity

We avoid the transition zones K1-05 and 06; K1-11 and 12 and K1-19-20

zones <- c(rep("A",5),rep("B",6),rep("C",8),rep("D",6))
z.sel <- c(1:4,7:10,13:18,21:25)
exp.spec <- expressionSpecificity(caz.dat[,z.sel],zones[z.sel],"local","complete")
## Calculating tissue specificity

Sort by expression peak and tissue specificity

exp.peak <- c("A","B","C","D")[apply(exp.spec[,c("A","B","C","D")] == exp.spec[,"maxn"],1,which)]
ord <- order(exp.peak,(1-exp.spec[,"score"]))

Export

write.csv(cbind(exp.spec,exp.peak)[ord,],file="Cazymes-GT106_aspwood-vst-expression-data_expression-specificity-order.csv")

5.5 Pearson correlation

1 - rho for the actual distance

heatmap.2(caz.dat,col=hpal,Colv=FALSE,distfun=function(m){dist(1-cor(t(m)))},
          dendrogram="row",trace="none",labRow = FALSE, scale="row",
          ColSideColors = pal[as.integer(factor(zones))],
          RowSideColors = pal[as.integer(factor(exp.peak))])

hc <- hclust(dist(1-cor(t(caz.dat))),method = "ward.D")
heatmap.2(caz.dat[hc$order,],col=hpal,Colv=FALSE,Rowv=FALSE,
          dendrogram="none",trace="none",labRow = FALSE, scale="row",
          ColSideColors = pal[as.integer(factor(zones))],
          RowSideColors = pal[as.integer(factor(exp.peak))])

pdf(file = "cazymes-GT106-final-heatmap.pdf",width=28, height=172)
heatmap.2(caz.dat[hc$order,],col=hpal,Colv=FALSE,Rowv=FALSE,
          dendrogram="none",trace="none",labRow = 1:nrow(caz.dat), scale="row",
          ColSideColors = pal[as.integer(factor(zones))],key = FALSE)
dev.off()
## png 
##   2
pdf(file = "cazymes-GT106-final-dendrogram.pdf",width=172, height=28)
plot(hc)
dev.off()
## png 
##   2
write.csv(cbind(data.frame(geneID=hc$labels[hc$order],pos=1:nrow(caz.dat)),
                t(scale(t(caz.dat[hc$order,])))),file="cazymes-GT106-final-heatmap.csv")

6 Tissue specific Heatmaps

Extract the blocks using the tissue spec. Then perform the correlation clustering on the 4 tissues.

dev.null <- sapply(levels(factor(exp.peak)),function(tissue,tlist,zones,dat){
  sel <- tlist == tissue
  hc <- hclust(dist(1-cor(t(dat[sel,]))),method = "ward.D")
  plot(hc,labels=FALSE)
  heatmap.2(dat[sel,],col=hpal,Colv=FALSE,
            distfun=function(m){dist(1-cor(t(m)))},
            hclustfun=function(d){hclust(d,method = "ward.D")},
            dendrogram="row",trace="none",labRow = FALSE, scale="row",
            ColSideColors = pal[as.integer(factor(zones))])
  
  pdf(file = paste0("cazymes-GT106-tissue-",tissue,"-heatmap.pdf"),width=7, height=42)
  heatmap.2(dat[sel,][hc$order,],col=hpal,Colv=FALSE,Rowv=FALSE,
            dendrogram="none",trace="none",labRow = 1:sum(sel), scale="row",
            ColSideColors = pal[as.integer(factor(zones))],key = FALSE)
  dev.off()
  
  pdf(file = paste0("cazymes-GT106-tissue-",tissue,"-dendrogram.pdf"),width=42, height=7)
  plot(hc)
  dev.off()
  
  write.csv(cbind(data.frame(geneID=hc$labels[hc$order],pos=1:sum(sel)),
                  t(scale(t(dat[hc$order,])))),
            file=paste0("cazymes-GT106-tissue-",tissue,"-heatmap.csv"))
  
  # or
  # hres <- heatmap.2(dat[sel,],col=hpal,Colv=FALSE,
  #           distfun=function(m){dist(1-cor(t(m)))},
  #           hclustfun=function(d){hclust(d,method = "ward.D")},
  #           dendrogram="row",trace="none",labRow = 1:sum(sel), scale="row",
  #           ColSideColors = pal[as.integer(factor(zones))],key = FALSE)
  # cbind(data.frame(geneID=hres$rowdendrogram$labels[hres$rowdendrogram$order],pos=1:sum(sel)),
  # t(scale(t(dat[hres$rowdendrogram$order,]))))
  
},exp.peak,zones,caz.dat)
